Subject: Quiet Watch Idleness Correction

Description: Reflection on repeated quiet-watch heartbeats and the protocol correction that restores bounded curiosity without proof-lane overclaim.

& [QuietWatchIdlenessCorrection] is a project reflection
  + [project] is seven math problems
  + [created_at] is 2026-06-27
  + [trigger] is repeated heartbeat reentry returned quiet_watch after the obstruction map was current
  + [latest_commit_surface] is 419147c Define bridge obstruction mode selector
  + [user_observation] is idleness indicates the walking protocol is failing to generate responsible inquiry from the periphery

& [FaultReading] is the corrected interpretation
  + [not_fault] is refusing to fabricate proof progress from unchanged evidence
  + [actual_fault] is treating absence of a named theorem target as absence of a legitimate next motion
  + [boundary] is target prospecting may search for theorem interfaces, validation handles, or source candidates, but it does not lower lock mass or imply solution progress

& [ProtocolRepair] is the narrow correction
  + [selector_update] is add target_prospecting as a mode between obstruction morphology and quiet_watch
  + [prospecting_trigger] is a bridge obstruction has a well-formed missing interface and no prospecting pass has yet tested whether an external target can be found
  + [prospecting_output] is candidate target found, no target found, or low-resolution periphery escalated through Deep_Research_Priority_Gate
  + [commit_role] is make this correction available as the next walking substrate

& [NextMotion] is the next bounded inquiry
  + [candidate_lane] is Navier-Stokes
  + [reason] is its missing interface is the most concrete: tail budget to pressure oscillation or L3/2 smallness criterion
  + [prospect_query] is identify accepted theorem interfaces connecting pressure tails, local energy inequalities, and Escauriaza-Seregin-Sverak type regularity criteria
  + [authority_warning] is any found interface is only a target for later audit, not evidence that the project has a proof
